  "body": "## !! WAITING ON RELEASE CANDIDATE !!\r\n\r\nThis issue is presently on-hold until the specification is stable.\r\n\r\n## Description\r\n\r\nThis is a \"mega issue\" which contains multiple discreet tasks. Mega issues exist to avoid cluttering the issues page a multitude of small tasks.\r\n\r\nIf you wish to work on one of these tasks, comment below and a maintainer will break the task out into a separate issue.\r\n\r\n## Per-slot processing\r\n\r\nThe [Per-slot processing](https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/master/specs/core/0_beacon-chain.md#per-slot-processing) defines the processing that should occur for each slot, regardless or if there is a block for that slot or not.\r\n\r\nPer-slot processing calls per-epoch processing (a separate set of functions), but a cursory glance indicates that per-slot processing does not depend upon per-epoch processing. Therefore it should be fine to develop them separately and link them at a later stage.\r\n\r\n## Mega-issue tasks\r\n\r\n- Core, basic logic:\r\n    - Updating `latest_block`, `latest_hash`, `slot`, etc.\r\n    - Checking for a block, processing it if it exists or increment `randao_skips` if not.\r\n- Proposer signature checking.\r\n- RANDAO processing.\r\n- PoW receipt root processing.\r\n- Process proposer slashings (blocked on #100 - slashing structs).\r\n- Process Casper slashings (blocked on #100 - slashing structs).\r\n- ~~Validate attestations~~ Included in #85.\r\n- Process deposits (blocked on #81).\r\n- Process exits (blocked on #106).\r\n- Eject validations (blocked on #106)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
